    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Calamus parvifructus are calamus tincture, calamus infusion, calamus tea, calamus oil, and calamus extract. Calamus tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the root in a solvent, often ethanol or glycerin, to capture its bioactive compounds. Calamus infusion is a liquid preparation made by steeping the dried root in hot water, releasing its volatile oils and flavonoids. Calamus tea is a more diluted version of the infusion, made by steeping the root in cold water or as a tea bag. Calamus oil and calamus extract are concentrated forms of the plant's essential oils and bioactive compounds, often used in aromatherapy and as a medicinal supplement.",
